This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it deals with improving the localization of autonomous vehicles. It also involves the integration of sensor data, which is a common problem in robotics. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it mentions visual/Lidar odometry. 

Machine learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a novel IMU integration model. 

The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with the integration of different sensors to improve the accuracy of localization. 

Finally, Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new approach to integrating IMU data, which could be considered an AI technique.
